---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-noida.html" headerVariant="guide">

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">Local Solar Guide · Noida, Uttar Pradesh</div>
<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">Rooftop Solar in Noida</h1>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Noida homeowners are cutting PVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies. This guide covers costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Check My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</section>

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">PVVNL</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Paschimanchal / UPPCL</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Noida</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Strong Solar Potential</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Noida receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day — comfortably above the threshold for financially viable rooftop solar. The NCR plains geography means most residential rooftops are well-suited for panel installation with minimal obstructions.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">High Electricity Bills in Summer</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Noida summers drive heavy air conditioning use, pushing PVVNL bills to their highest of the year. Solar output peaks through these same months, creating maximum financial benefit precisely when your bills are largest.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Rising PVVNL Tariffs</h3><p class="text-slate-600">PVVNL domestic tariffs have risen over successive UP regulatory cycles. Installing solar now locks in a portion of your electricity at zero marginal cost for the system's 25-year life, providing a hedge against future tariff increases.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Eligibility</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Noida homeowners with a PVVNL residential connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy. PVVNL maintains an empanelled installer list for Noida and Gautam Buddha Nagar on pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PVVNL Net Metering in Noida</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Noida homeowners under PVVNL.</p>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via PVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your installer must be empanelled with PVVNL under the PM Surya Ghar scheme. Verify on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to PVVNL</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to PVVNL with system technical details. Most empanelled installers handle this on your behalf.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">PVVNL Technical Inspection</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A PVVNL engineer inspects the installation to verify grid safety compliance. Timelines in Noida typically range from two to four weeks depending on DISCOM workload.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your existing PVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter measuring both import and export. A one-time meter replacement fee may apply.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once commissioned by PVVNL, surplus solar exported to the grid earns credits on your monthly PVVNL electricity bill.</p></div></div>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">See our <a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a> for a full explanation of how credits work on your bill.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Choosing the Right System Size in Noida</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly PVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly PVVNL Bill</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area Needed</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th></tr></thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr><td class="p-4">₹800 – ₹2,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="1kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">1kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">80–120 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small homes, limited roof</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹1,500 – ₹3,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small families, 2BHK</td></tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50"><td class="p-4">₹2,500 – ₹5,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td><td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Medium families, 3BHK</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹4,000 – ₹7,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Larger homes, heavy AC use</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a> for the full methodology.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Noida</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Noida homeowners with a PVVNL connection can apply for the central subsidy through pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW at lower per-kW rate</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div></div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as a Noida Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your PVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select a PVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal's list</li>
<li>3. Get system installed, net metering connected, PVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited to your bank account — typically weeks to months</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">Subsidy amounts are subject to government policy. Verify current rates at pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
</div>
<div class="mt-4"><a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →</a></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Noida Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">We help homeowners across Noida and Gautam Buddha Nagar understand solar options and connect with PVVNL-empanelled installers.</p>
<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{["Sector 18", "Sector 44", "Sector 50", "Sector 62", "Sector 76", "Sector 93", "Sector 100", "Sector 120", "Sector 137", "Sector 143", "Noida Extension", "Greater Noida West", "Dadri Road", "Expressway Sectors"].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Noida Solar</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Noida?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Most residential areas in Noida and Gautam Buddha Nagar are served by <strong>PVVNL (Paschimanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a UPPCL subsidiary covering western UP. All net metering applications for PVVNL-connected homes are processed through PVVNL.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering with PVVNL in Noida?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation by a PVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering application to PVVNL. PVVNL inspects the system and installs a bi-directional meter. The process typically takes two to four weeks in Noida.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Noida?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Noida homeowners with a PVVNL connection are eligible. Use a PVVNL-empanelled installer and apply at pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current subsidy amounts before applying.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Noida homes?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">For typical Noida homes with monthly PVVNL bills of ₹2,000–₹5,000, a 2kW to 3kW system covers a significant portion of electricity use. Homes with heavy summer AC use and bills above ₹5,000 often benefit from 3kW to 5kW systems.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Noida?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pre-subsidy cost for a quality on-grid system in Noida typically ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW. After PM Surya Ghar central subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Compare quotes from at least two PVVNL-empanelled installers.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Can apartment residents in Noida get solar?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Apartment societies in Noida can install solar on common terraces under group net metering — credits are distributed to participating flat owners' bills. Individual flat owners without dedicated roof access should work through their RWA. See our <a href="learn/rooftop-solar-apartments.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">apartment solar guide</a> for details.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-10">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
<p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Also serving homeowners in <a href="rooftop-solar-ghaziabad.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Ghaziabad</a> and <a href="rooftop-solar-meerut.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Meerut</a> — both under PVVNL with the same net metering process. <a href="cities.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">View all city guides →</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Helpful Guides for Noida Homeowners</h2>
<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Subsidies</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">PM Surya Ghar Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Billing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Net Metering Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/solar-inverter-types-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Equipment</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Solar Inverter Types</div></a>
<a href="learn/how-to-choose-solar-installer.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Installers</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">How to Choose an Installer</div></a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-[2rem] p-10">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">See How Much You Can Save in Noida</h2>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-8">Get a personalised solar savings estimate based on your PVVNL bill — in under 60 seconds.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Calculate My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
